      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You should *not* mix diazepam with red wine or any alcohol. Alcohol can intensify the sedative effects of diazepam, which can lead to excessive drowsiness, dizziness, or even dangerous respiratory depression. For sleep, stick to the dosage your doctor prescribed and consider non-pharmaceutical aids like warm milk instead. If you have concerns about interactions, always consult with your prescribing physician first.",
