      "content": "While some people may do this, it is medically unsound to treat it as a mild booster. Alcohol and diazepam are both central nervous system depressants, meaning they work on the same pathways to slow your body down. Even \"just a few sips\" can lower the threshold for severe side effects, like dangerous sedation. For the safest and most predictable sleep, it's important to strictly adhere to your prescription without adding alcohol.",
